{"id": 5864, "title": "Ticket #5864: Threading issue in python binding", "description": "<blockquote>\nHad a user report that the module lock is release too early during <code>query</code>.  While the module lock is held (which releases the python GIL), a copy is made of a python object.\n\n<p>That invokes interpreter code while the GIL is not held: if there's another thread executing python at the same time, this can result in a crash.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Sep-23 16:10</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d57f99a1c6eff2e208a40ea364118c35967f20bd\">[49284]</a></span>: Version history for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5864\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5864'); return false;\" title=\"Threading issue in python binding\">#5864</a></span>  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Aug-23 21:53</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/a92c11b6b2c06ade0cdb691f4ae14e5de535930f\">[49068]</a></span>: Fix use of python API without GIL. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5864\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5864'); return false;\" title=\"Threading issue in python binding\">#5864</a></span> Make sure that the GIL is held when we call any python code - even when calling a copy constructor Committer: Brian Bockelman  (By Chetan Reddy )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2016-Sep-26 09:54", "status": "resolved", "created": "2016-Aug-23 21:37", "fixed_version": "2016-Aug-23 21:37", "broken_version": "", "priority": "4", "subsystem": "PythonBinding", "assigned_to": "tim", "derived_from": "", "creator": "bbockelm", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "bbockelm@cse.unl.edu", "due_date": ""}